---
// Motivation.astro — sets up the problem before Method
const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<section id="motivation" class="content-section motivation-section">
  <div class="section-container">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">The problem</p>
    <h2 class="motivation-title">Why is cross-domain compositing hard?</h2>

    <p class="motivation-intro">
      Cross-domain compositing is a challenging task that requires placing a
      foreground object onto a background across heterogeneous domains,
      <em>preserving the identity</em> of the foreground while
      <em>transferring the style</em> of the background for seamless
      integration.
    </p>

    <div class="motivation-grid">
      <div class="motivation-text">
        <span class="motivation-item-number">1</span>
        <h3 class="motivation-item-heading">Lack of large-scale paired data</h3>
        <p>
          Existing cross-domain compositing approaches largely rely on
          <em>training-free blending and refinement strategies</em>, partly due
          to the lack of <em>large-scale paired datasets</em>, limiting the
          development of <em>training-based solutions</em>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="motivation-figure">
        <div class="image-frame">
          <img src={`${basePath}assets/motivation/1.png`} alt="Dataset comparison — paired data scale" />
        </div>
        <figcaption>
          <b>Table 1.</b> Unlike <b>prior</b> datasets that support either
          stylization or compositing in <b>isolation</b>, <b>ours</b> is the
          only dataset that <b>jointly supports</b>, while providing real-image
          supervision without <i>generative artifacts</i>.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="motivation-grid">
      <div class="motivation-text">
        <span class="motivation-item-number">2</span>
        <h3 class="motivation-item-heading">
          Recent strong semantic encoders such as DINOv3, largely underexplored
          for stylization
        </h3>
        <p>
          Recent self-supervised encoders such as <em>DINOv3</em> have
          demonstrated transferability across classification and segmentation.
          Yet their capacity as a <em>style encoder</em> remains
          <em>largely underexplored</em>. Naive use of DINO leads to
          <i>content leakage</i> (Figure 1).
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="motivation-figure">
        <div class="image-frame">
          <img src={`${basePath}assets/motivation/2.png`} alt="DINOv3 as a style encoder — placeholder" />
        </div>
        <figcaption>
          <b>Figure 1.</b> <b>(b)</b> <b>Naive DINO</b> focuses on human regions,
          causing <i>content leakage</i>.<br />
          <b>(c)</b> <b>Our ChameleonEncoder</b> (style head) <b>globally</b>
          distributes attention, capturing background style rather than
          content, for faithful compositing.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="motivation-grid">
      <div class="motivation-text">
        <span class="motivation-item-number">3</span>
        <h3 class="motivation-item-heading">
          Naive style injection across all tokens is suboptimal
        </h3>
        <p>
          The <em>background already</em> preserves its own appearance
          statistics in the VAE latent, so naively allowing the style token
          to attend to <em>all latent tokens</em> (including those of the
          background) is <i>suboptimal</i>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="motivation-figure">
        <div class="image-frame">
          <img src={`${basePath}assets/motivation/3.png`} alt="Style injection — placeholder" />
        </div>
        <figcaption>
          <b>Figure 2.</b> <b>(a)</b> Without <b>STAG</b>, the style token
          attends uniformly across all latent tokens, which is
          <i>suboptimal</i>. <b>(b)</b> With <b>STAG</b>, attention
          concentrates on the foreground region (e.g., the Eiffel Tower),
          enabling effective harmonization.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .motivation-section {
    background-color: #ffffff;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(31, 94, 54, 0.12);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(31, 94, 54, 0.12);
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #2D8F47;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .motivation-title {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1F5E36;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    max-width: 820px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .motivation-intro {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #333;
    max-width: 820px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
  }

  .motivation-intro em {
    color: #1F5E36;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .motivation-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .motivation-grid + .motivation-grid {
    margin-top: 3.5rem;
  }


  .motivation-text p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #333;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .motivation-text em {
    color: #1F5E36;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .motivation-text i {
    color: #c0392b;
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
  }

  .motivation-item-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2.25rem;
    height: 2.25rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #1F5E36;
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .motivation-item-heading {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1F5E36;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .motivation-figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .motivation-figure img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .image-frame {
    background-color: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.25rem 0.15rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .motivation-figure figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .motivation-figure figcaption b {
    color: #1F5E36;
  }

  .motivation-figure figcaption .caption-warn {
    color: #c0392b;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .motivation-figure figcaption i {
    color: #c0392b;
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .motivation-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }
    .motivation-title {
      font-size: 1.55rem;
    }
  }
</style>
